owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A mental state is a state of mind
The way a person or animal acts or behaves
Affective State
Emotion is the result of a persons exposure to an internal or external stimulus and is expressed by changes in facial expression, gesture, voice or physiological parameters
Mood is an emotional state that affects the experience and behavior of a person. It has a lower intensity but a longer duration than emotion
emotional state
Human Needs are necessities for the development of physical and mental growth of individuals
Personality is defined as an individual pattern of affect, behavior, cognition and goals over time and space
Relating to the body of a person instead of the mind
a view of or attitude toward a situation or event; an opinion
Refers to how people experience the quality of their lives
An agent (eg. person, group, software or physical artifact).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Agent
